race.comment: KIMBERLEY SECRETS (1) consistent mare who doesn't know how to run a bad race. Proven at this level and should get conditions to suit with Keatings' 3kg claim. Will roll forward from the sticky gate and prove hard to run down. COUPLES RETREAT (3) has gone to a new level this preparation and finally drawn a decent marble tonight. Comes out of a very strong contest when third to Spywire and Hawker Hall over 1000m at Kembla Grange in BM78 class. Form has been franked and gets every chance. CAFFE FLORIAN (8) smart Snitzel filly who drifted back from her wide draw before launching late with a slick Maiden win over 1100m at this track. Has the upside to play a role in this stronger contest. FLIGHTCREW (4) tough mare set to peak fourth-up. Chased hard when a gritty third to Mafia over 1250m at this track. Will appreciate the fast tempo and is capable of finishing over the top of these.
